text:
For new fans: 
(in age order)

Scoups(Seungcheol): All black outfit, black sweatpants with white lettering on side, black tshirt with white design, black cap
Jeonghan: Camo pants, grey shirt, white cap
Joshua: All white outfit, red nike shoes, Black cap
Jun(Junhui): All black outfit, black tshirt with white arrows on back and some blue, grey cap
Hoshi(Soonyoung): Grey and black sweatpants, grey in front, black in back, black muscle shirt, short blonde hair
Wonwoo: All white outfit, white cap and white mask on chin
Woozi(Jihoon): All black outfit, black shorts, black tshirt
DK(Dokyeom/Seokmin): Blue ripped jeans, black baggy shirt, black beanie
Mingyu: All black outfit, black tshirt black shorts, black cap
The8(Minghao): Black pants, white, red, and black jacket, red hair
Seungkwan: Blue shoes, black pants, black jacket over white shirt, blonde hair
Vernon(Hansol): Red converse, jeans, black tshirt, black cap
Dino(Chan): Black/grey pants, white tshirt

Scoups is the leader
Units are: 
Hiphop unit: Scoups, Wonwoo, Mingyu, Vernon
Performnce Unit: Hoshi,Jun, The8, Dino
Vocal Unit: Joshua, Jeonghan, Woozi, Dokyeom, Seungkwan

Enjoy!

ジョンハンがほんまにうまい。目立つ。体の向きと、使い方がめっちゃうまい。姿勢の角度、肩の使い方が綺麗。スングァン、ドギョムもうまい。スングァンは動きが大きくて綺麗。ドギョムは動きが滑らか。
ホシは勢いがあってすごくいい。

Jeonghan’s dance is really good and beautiful. The direction and way of his body is very good. He stands out. Seungkwan and DK are also wonderful. Seungkwan expresses with big move. 
DK’s move is so smooth. 
Hoshi is powerful.

author: @eyza8107
text: Eisa capturing all the attention all on him and then suddenly spreading  it like a Domino throughout Seventeen made me realize once again why they are called “The Performance Powerhouse of Kpop.” Coming from RWY’s choreo where it feels like each second is a time to lose something, RWY keeps us out of breath, hanging by the edge of our seats, running together to reach something that could disappear quickly.  HOT, on the other hand, exudes such smoothness and self-assurance. The attention to detail to every beat makes the overall choreo radiate confidence which is complimented with the power of every movement. In conclusion, Seventeen are confident in their art & Hot & they’re very aware of that.
